text: The white-spotted moray (Gymnothorax johnsoni) is a moray eel found in the western Indian Ocean.Gymnothorax johnsoni at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Smith in 1962.Common names for Gymnothorax johnsoni at www.fishbase.org. ==References== johnsoni Category:Fish described in 1962
